Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Renal function is mildly impaired (elevated serum creatinine). Urinalysis shows glucosuria and proteinuria with low specific gravity, suggesting possible renal tubular dysfunction or early diabetic nephropathy. Blood glucose and HbA1c are at the upper limit of normal, indicating prediabetes. Urine is cloudy and brown with ammoniacal odor, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Recommend further evaluation of renal function and glycemic control.
